{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, MuTAP [32] utilizes surviving mutants from initial test runs as contextual feedback, instructing the LLM to generate new tests capable of killing these specific mutants, thereby shifting the testing objective from coverage to fault detection.",
    "Another one is retrieval-augmented generation (RAG).",
    "This technique enhances prompts by retrieving relevant information to mitigate issues related to outdated model knowledge or a lack of project-specific context [49].",
    "For example, APT [171] retrieves test cases for methods that are structurally or behaviorally similar from the codebase.",
    "These retrieved cases serve as high-quality, in-context few-shot examples that guide the model to adhere to projectspecific testing patterns and API usage."
  ]
}